My Quick Recall

- Session = Server remembers me.
- JWT = I carry my identity with me.
- Redis is commonly used to store sessions.
- JWT = Header + Payload + Signature.
- Payload is readable, so never store secrets.
- Access Token = Short life.
- Refresh Token = Gets a new Access Token.
- Sessions are easier to revoke.
- JWTs are easier to scale.

One-line Memory Trick

"Session asks the server, JWT shows a signed ID card."